for a huge portion of the last year, Mother Nature is what took care of me. the water & tree u see in this video were right across the street from the first home I ever lived in by myself
that experience alone taught me so much, and whenever it was extra hard, I would come to this land. i would rest my back on this tree & reground into myself. moments like these are what taught me to self-soothe. i learned to trust myself more, to give myself permission to take up space, and most importantly, that my alone-time can be a safe-space for my inner-child. all of me is welcome here. thank u 2022 for all the lessons that helped me come to these truths. thank u Hawai’i for the role u played in my journey. I am so happy I decided to fly back to this place for a week, I think this is exactly what my heart needed. 🧡

freeing february 🦋
the themes of the month have been acceptance, grief, reconnecting with myself, letting my heart open wider, surrender &looking forward. sometimes lessons get delivered to us in interesting ways. sometimes things bubble to the surface so we can get to know certain sides of ourself on a deeper level. this journey is so personal, so special, & it’s between u and u. this is about healing. this is about having the courage to trust.
clarity is coming , closure is coming , and so is a brand new month that I welcome with open arms 🙏🏽 sending love

earlier today I did this post where I wrote “freeing February 🦋” followed by some themes of the month… as i re-looked at that post, a part of me wanted to be like han…. BFFR.
in all honesty, this was the most disheveling month I’ve had in awhile. I had to face something that I was pretty uncomfortable facing. and for a large portion of the month I was doing nothing but be hard on myself & gaslight myself into thinking all the inner-work I’ve done so far was fake // I’m a joke of a person // all this other self-deprecating bs. I was convinced I had taken so many steps backwards that there was no way to continue forward (funny how our emotions can make us feel that way huh?). I struggled with my eating. I struggled with finding meaning. I struggled with letting those i loved in. I felt lonely. Trapped in my own head. And struggled with offering empathy towards myself. 
the thing with running from urself is that it never really works out, at some point u gotta face ur shit head on. And although I am still very much in a processing phase, it only felt right to share this. We all have lives behind the screens and those lives can be messy at times. I’m
trying to remind myself that my mess is my message & that there’s room for all sides of me to exist.
❤️‍🩹 if u read all that .. ty for holding space. ily

(I love it when my life’s like this)

I've always strived to keep my platform a safe space, shielded from the outside world. but when the world is on fire and my people are dying and I stay silent, then that would no longer keep my page a safe space for all, would it?

I haven’t said this on here before, but I am half-Palestinian. In 1948, my teta and jedo (grandma and grandpa) faced an unimaginable choice: to stay in their homeland and face peril, or leave with just the clothes on their backs. They chose survival and found refuge in Lebanon, and then later Jordan, where my Dad still lives
I love the Middle East and I love my culture. from age 15-19 my culture was ripped away from me and I have been finding my way back since. still the roots of my heritage always remained strong in me 

I’ve always tried to show u guys my heart, and right now my heart has been begging me to speak about what is happening in Gaza. I worry that no matter what i say it will be misconstrued, but to stay silent isn’t any option anymore

I want a ceasefire!!! I want peace!!! I want liberation!! 
Me supporting a free Palestine doesn’t make me anti-semitic, and it definitely doesn’t mean I am in support of Hamas or lack empathy and grief for the Israeli lives’ lost on October 7th, 2023. But using that as an excuse to fund and justify the complete obliteration of Gaza and all its people is incomprehensible.

I urge u to educate yourself on the history here as well as what the last couple weeks in Gaza has looked like for them. This land has been colonized with countless lives lost for decades. Let's remember this is not an isolated issue - indigenous groups worldwide share similar stories. 

I will always try to listen and stand in solidarity with all who cry for justice, whether it's Palestinians, Native Americans, Congolese, Sudanese, Hawaiians, or any other marginalized community 🙏🏽

My heart aches. I feel the pain of my ancestors, I feel for the endless misunderstandings, I feel for those who feel like their cries and pleas are landing on deaf ears 

No words will ever be enough, but I stand with you. Let love win. Love will always win❤️❤️🍉

Much mahalo to Hawai’i. I hold these lands with so much reverence in my heart. Forever grateful for the relationship I get to have with this place🌕🙏🏽
